e max-w-full"><h2>What Is a Week Number?</h2><p>A week number represents th=
e specific week of the year, from week 1 to week 52 (or 53).</p><p>In the I=
SO 8601 calendar format, weeks start with Monday and end on Sunday. Monday =
is the first day of each week, while Sunday is the seventh day. According t=
o this week numbering system, the first week of the year is the week contai=
ning the first Thursday of the year. This means Week 1 begins on the first =
Monday before or after that Thursday.</p><p>Since a year has 365 days (366 =
in leap years), some years include a 53rd week. This happens when January 1=
 falls on a Thursday in a regular year, or on a Wednesday or Thursday in a =
leap year.</p><h2>What Is the Week Number Page?</h2><p>On this page, you ca=
n do many operations related to weeks:</p><ul><li>View the current week no,=
 its date range, and how many weeks left in this year.</li><li>Find the num=
ber of the week for a specific date.</li><li>See the date range for any wee=
k in a specific year.</li></ul><p><strong>Note</strong>: The page updates e=
very minute to provide you with the most accurate information. If you check=
 our <a href=3D"https://onlinealarmkur.com/clock/en/">online clock</a> page=
 and observe when the clock hits <em>00:00 on Monday</em> (the beginning of=
 the new week), you will see that the numbers here will update within a min=
ute.</p><h2>How to Use This Tool</h2><p>The page currently offers three ope=
rations.</p><h3>Find out the current week number</h3><ol><li>Switch to "Cur=
rent Week Number" tab, which is the default tab when you visit the page.</l=
i><li>You will see the number of the week and its corresponding date range.=
</li><li>You can also see how many weeks are left in this year.</li></ol><h=
3>Convert date to week number</h3><ol><li>Switch to "Date to Week Number" t=
ab.</li><li>Click the "Date" input to open the calendar and select a <a hre=
f=3D"https://onlinealarmkur.com/date/en/">date</a>.</li><li>Click the "Conv=
ert to Week Number" button.</li><li>You will see the number of the week tha=
t corresponds to your selected date.</li></ol><h3>Convert week number to da=
te</h3><ol><li>Switch to "Week Number to Date" tab.</li><li>Enter the numbe=
r of the week for conversion (1 for first week, up to 53)</li><li>Enter the=
 year (defaults to current year).</li><li>Click the "Convert to Date" butto=
n.</li><li>You will see the date range for your selected week.</li></ol></a=
